      "span_text": "PON1 mRNA expression is significantly repressed during an acute-phase response in rabbits, in apoA-II transgenic mice, in C57BL/6J(B6) mice fed an atherogenic diet, and in cultured HepG2 cells treated with the cytokines tumor necrosis factor and interleukin-1 or MM-LDL. Because, unlike PON1, PON3 mRNA expression is not altered by either ox-PAPC in HepG2 cells ( Figure 5A ) or a high-fat diet in the livers of C57BL/6 mice ( Figure 5B and 5C ), PON1 and PON3 may play distinct roles in the prevention of atherosclerosis."
